haviour,\" he&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; text-decoration-line: none; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #326891 !important;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/Knightcartoons/status/1039056385462349825\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">wrote&nbsp;</a>on Twitter.</p>\r\n<div class=\"comment_story\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; float: right; position: relative; width: 90px; height: 60px; margin: 7px 0px 15px 15px; display: table; background: #326891; border-radius: 5px; text-align: center; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; color: #ffffff; text-transform: uppercase; opacity: 0.5; transition: all 0.3s ease-in 0s; transform: scale(1);\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; display: table-cell; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"ndtv-detailp-comments-count\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; display: block; padding: 5px;\">1 COMMENT</span></span></div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 15px; padding: 0px;\">Nobody seems to buying his argument - the Internet is deeply divided on how they view Serena Williams\' conduct on court but it is as one on the subject of the distasteful and offensive cartoon.</p>\r\n</div>', '0', 0, 'published', 1);
